The paper deals with the problem of partial monitoring, which is a subfield of machine learning and game theory. The paper proposes new algorithms and analyzes existing ones, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning subfield (cs.LG). The paper also solves an open problem posed by Bartok et al. [2014], which indicates that it belongs to the game theory subfield (cs.GT). The paper discusses the regret bounds of the algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the artificial intelligence subfield (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of game structures, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures subfield (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves information theory, which suggests that it belongs to the information theory subfield (cs.IT).
